      /* TESSLightbulbsGraphs.do */
/** @author Allcott and Taubinsky*/
* "The Lightbulb Paradox"


*******************************************************************

/* GRAPHS */
/* Non-parametric treatment effect graph */
use Calculations/PreppedTESSData.dta,clear
** Test whether effects are any different across the baseline demand curve
reg WTP2 c.T#c.WTP1 WTP1_C*  [pweight=Weight], robust, if WTP1<=9&WTP1>=-9

** Test whether all AMTs are equal
reg WTP2 TxWTP1_S* WTP1_C* [pweight=Weight], robust, if WTP1<=9&WTP1>=-9
testparm TxWTP1_S*, equal


/* Demand curve and conditional average treatment effect graph */
	** Heterogeneous treatment effects by initial WTP (different marginal internalities)
levelsof WTP1, local(levels)
local i = 1
foreach w of local levels {
	capture noisily xi: reg WTP2 T i.WTP1 [pweight=Weight], robust, if WTP1smooth==`w' // capture because WTP1smooth may not equal WTP1. Need to control for WTP1 also because this might vary within WTP1Smooth, and failing to control gives incorrect results.
	capture local tau_`i' = _b[T]
	capture local SEtau_`i' = _se[T]
	capture local N_`i' = e(N)
	
	** Alternative Topcodes 1-4
	forvalues t = 1/4 {
		capture noisily xi: reg WTP2_top`t' T i.WTP1 [pweight=Weight], robust, if WTP1smooth==`w'
		capture local tau_top`t'_`i' = _b[T]
		capture local SEtau_top`t'_`i' = _se[T]
	}
	
	
	**** Get demand curves
	** Baseline and endline:
		* Note: to make sure they are comparable (and to divide all by the same total weight Qtotal), these demand curves include only consumers with valid baseline and endline WTPs.
	* Baseline
	sum Weight if WTP1>=`w'&WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.
	local Q1_`i' = r(mean)*r(N)
	
	* Endline
	sum Weight if WTP2>=`w'&WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.
	local Q2_`i' = r(mean)*r(N)
	
	* Get T and C
	forvalues t = 0/1 {
		sum Weight if WTP2>=`w'&WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.&T==`t'
		local Q2`t'_`i' = r(mean)*r(N)
	}
	** Get TP=1 and TP == 0
	forvalues t = 0/1 {
		sum Weight if WTP2>=`w'&WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.&T==1&TP==`t'
		local Q2TP`t'_`i' = r(mean)*r(N)
	}
	
	** Get T EndlineOnly=1
	sum Weight if WTP2>=`w'&WTP2!=.&T==1&EndlineOnly==1
	local Q2EO_`i' = r(mean)*r(N)
	
	local i = `i' + 1
}

sum Weight if WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.
local Qtotal = r(mean)*r(N)

forvalues t=0/1 {
	sum Weight if WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.&T==`t'
	local Qtotal`t' = r(mean)*r(N)
	sum Weight if WTP1!=.&WTP2!=.&T==1&TP==`t'
	local QtotalTP`t' = r(mean)*r(N)
}
sum Weight if WTP2!=.&T==1&EndlineOnly==1
local QtotalEO = r(mean)*r(N)
	
clear 
set obs 30
gen WTP = .
gen tau = .
gen SEtau = .
gen N = .
gen Q1 = .
gen Share1 = .
gen Q2 = .
gen Share2 = .
forvalues t = 0/1 {
	gen Q2`t' = .
	gen Share2`t' = .
	gen Q2TP`t' = .
	gen Share2TP`t' = .
}
gen Q2EO = .
gen Share2EO = .
forvalues t=1/4 {
	gen tau_top`t' = .
	gen SEtau_top`t' = .
}

local i = 1
foreach w of local levels {
	replace WTP = `w' if _n==`i'
	
	* Treatment effects
	capture replace tau = `tau_`i'' if _n==`i'
	capture replace SEtau = `SEtau_`i'' if _n==`i'
	forvalues t=1/4 {
		capture replace tau_top`t' = `tau_top`t'_`i'' if _n==`i'
		capture replace SEtau_top`t' = `SEtau_top`t'_`i'' if _n==`i'
	}
	
	* Demand curves
	replace N = `N_`i'' if _n==`i'
	replace Q1 = `Q1_`i'' if _n==`i'
	replace Share1 = Q1/`Qtotal' if _n==`i'
	replace Q2 = `Q2_`i'' if _n==`i'
	replace Share2 = Q2/`Qtotal' if _n==`i'
	forvalues t = 0/1 {
		* T vs. C
		replace Q2`t' = `Q2`t'_`i'' if _n==`i'
		replace Share2`t' = Q2`t'/`Qtotal`t'' if _n==`i'
		* Balanced vs. Positive Treatment
		replace Q2TP`t' = `Q2TP`t'_`i'' if _n==`i'
		replace Share2TP`t' = Q2TP`t'/`QtotalTP`t'' if _n==`i'
	}
	* EndlineOnly 1 vs. 0
	replace Q2EO = `Q2EO_`i'' if _n==`i'
	replace Share2EO = Q2EO/`QtotalEO' if _n==`i'
	local i = `i' + 1
}

** Graph the demand curves
*gen WTP_True = WTP+tau
** Pre vs. post
twoway (line WTP Share1) (line WTP Share2)
** PostT vs. postC
twoway (line WTP Share21) (line WTP Share20)
** Pre, postT, postC
twoway (line WTP Share1) (line WTP Share20) (line WTP Share21)
** Positive vs. Balanced (to see if this influences the rotation of demand.
twoway (line WTP Share2TP0) (line WTP Share2TP1) (line WTP Share20) 
** EO=1 vs. EO=0
twoway (line WTP Share2EO) (line WTP Share21) (line WTP Share20)


*** Graph the average marginal bias
* Graph for top-codes
line tau_top? WTP


** Final graph of main estimates
gen ci10 = tau-SEtau*1.65
gen ci90 = tau+SEtau*1.65

line tau ci10 ci90 WTP



** Export to excel

gsort -WTP
order  WTP Share1 tau ci10 ci90 
outsheet using Output/TESSWTPFigure.csv, comma names replace



/* Graph of pre-post changes */
use Calculations/PreppedTESSData.dta,clear
twoway (kdensity WTP2_WTP1 if T==1, bw(0.2)) (kdensity WTP2_WTP1 if T==0, bw(0.2))
collapse (sum) Weight, by(T WTP2_WTP1)
drop if WTP2_WTP1==.

forvalues t = 0/1 {
	sum Weight if T==`t'
	local T`t'total = r(mean)*r(N)
	replace Weight = Weight/`T`t'total' if T==`t'
}


reshape wide Weight, i(WTP2_WTP1) j(T) 
forvalues t = 0/1 {
	replace Weight`t' = 0 if Weight`t'==.
}

gen WTP2_WTP1Bucket = floor(WTP2_WTP1)
collapse (sum) Weight?, by(WTP2_WTP1Bucket)
order WTP2_WTP1Bucket Weight1 Weight0 
outsheet using Output/TESSWTPChangeFigure.csv, comma names replace
